## Why This Is Asked
Tests that exercise keyboard accessibility demonstrate familiarity with a11y concepts and deterministic testing approaches for beginners.

## Key Concepts
- Keyboard navigation and focus management
- ARIA roles and attributes (role=dialog, aria-label, aria-live)
- Test determinism with seeded localStorage and deterministic delays

## Code Example

```javascript
// Example test outline in Cypress
describe('Keyboard accessibility for notes', () => {
  it('navigates via Tab, opens modal, saves, edits, deletes, and persists', () => {
    // seed
    window.localStorage.setItem('notes', JSON.stringify([
      { id: 1, title: 'Note 1', body: 'Body 1' },
      { id: 2, title: 'Note 2', body: 'Body 2' }
    ]));

    cy.visit('/');

    // Tab through list and verify focus
    cy.get('[data-testid="note-item"]').first().focus();
    cy.focused().should('have.attr', 'role', 'listitem');

    // Open create modal with keyboard
    cy.get('[data-testid="create-button"]').focus().type('{enter}');
    cy.get('[role="dialog"]').should('be.visible');

    // Create note
    cy.get('[data-testid="note-title"]').type('New Note');
    cy.get('[data-testid="note-body"]').type('New Body');
    cy.get('[data-testid="save-button"]').click();

    // Edit existing note
    cy.get('[data-testid="note-item"]').first().focus().type('{enter}');
    cy.get('[data-testid="note-title"]').clear().type('Edited Title');
    cy.get('[data-testid="save-button"]').click();

    // Delete note
    cy.get('[data-testid="note-item"]').first().focus();
    cy.get('[data-testid="delete-button"]').click();

    // Verify persistence after reload
    cy.reload();
    cy.window().then(win => {
      const notes = JSON.parse(win.localStorage.getItem('notes'));
      expect(notes).to.have.length(2);
    });
  });
});
```

